Down further.

54:59.600 --> 55:02.080
Further further.

55:02.080 --> 55:03.960
More.

55:03.960 --> 55:05.960
More.

55:05.960 --> 55:07.960
There we go.

55:07.960 --> 55:09.880
Okay.

55:09.880 --> 55:10.880
Go one more.

55:10.880 --> 55:14.040
And then I'll go back to this because this is, okay.

55:14.040 --> 55:21.000
This came from the study that I mentioned before of kids whose parents were hospitalized

55:21.000 --> 55:24.800
for suicide attempts.

55:24.800 --> 55:28.280
And we used only drawings as a starting point.

55:28.280 --> 55:29.720
We didn't ask them about anything.

55:29.720 --> 55:33.560
And one of the things we became aware of as if the parents lied to them about what they

55:33.560 --> 55:37.800
were doing, while everything was perfectly evident, and then many of the kids knew, in

55:37.800 --> 55:40.960
fact, even knew when the parents were doing.

55:40.960 --> 55:47.680
This is a drawing of a youngster who drew his father, who was in the hospital, who had

55:47.680 --> 55:52.240
slashed up his neck and his wrists.

55:52.240 --> 55:57.640
And those are direct representations of his father's bandaged hands and his father's

55:57.640 --> 56:01.720
straggly beard, which was covering up everything else.

56:01.720 --> 56:10.080
Now there the manifest content is smashing in relation to its immediacy.

56:10.080 --> 56:17.600
But the further inquiry was to realize that there's more behind this.

56:17.600 --> 56:21.520
We knew he realized that we knew it was there, and so forth and so on.

56:21.520 --> 56:26.640
No matter how many people lied to him, at least we had some evidentiary base that this is his

56:26.640 --> 56:28.600
acknowledgment of it.

56:28.600 --> 56:32.480
So there the manifest content is useful to us.

56:32.480 --> 56:36.200
But it's not, didn't tell us what he was thinking, feeling and what have you.

56:36.200 --> 56:41.120
By the way, one of the outcomes of this study, which was then advanced later on at other

56:41.120 --> 56:47.000
places, Bob became a great student of trauma.

56:47.000 --> 56:53.000
He interviewed a lot of kids who was one parent killed the other right in the police station

56:53.000 --> 56:55.400
and used these drawing techniques.

56:55.400 --> 56:58.840
I just wanted to tell you about how useful it is.

56:58.840 --> 57:01.320
Go one back now.

57:01.320 --> 57:04.720
Okay.

57:04.720 --> 57:08.400
Let me tell you the background of this because I'm going to get to this drawing.

57:08.400 --> 57:13.960
It was a little girl, very shy, very tiring, five years of age.

57:13.960 --> 57:21.160
Her father, a surgeon, had brought it to see me many years ago.

57:21.160 --> 57:23.920
The family had suffered a loss.

57:23.920 --> 57:30.720
A relative of theirs had lost two children and a mother in a fire in a country home.

57:30.720 --> 57:35.640
And she knew about it, etc., and was having, wasn't sleeping very well.

57:35.640 --> 57:41.560
Well, her father brought her into the office after I had gotten some history and so forth

57:41.560 --> 57:43.480
from them separately.

57:43.480 --> 57:44.680
And she was very shy.

57:44.680 --> 57:47.080
She was hanging behind her father.

57:47.080 --> 57:50.520
She wasn't going to talk and so forth and so on.

57:50.520 --> 57:54.240
So I let them both come into the consulting room together.

57:54.240 --> 57:58.520
And I realized I wasn't going to get very far with her.

57:58.520 --> 58:02.080
I started peppering her with questions or doing anything.

58:02.080 --> 58:06.320
So I took a stack of paper and I said, I just read Winnicott and Winnicott has something

58:06.320 --> 58:07.320
called a squiggle game.

58:07.320 --> 58:10.360
You make a little squiggle and they finish it and then you take another sheet of paper

58:10.360 --> 58:11.560
and then we go further.

58:11.560 --> 58:13.760
We must have had 15 squiggles in the midst of it.

58:13.760 --> 58:16.680
I was brave enough to ask her father to go out.

58:16.680 --> 58:20.280
And he goes out and she stayed with me and she loosened up and she began talking about

58:20.280 --> 58:21.280
things.

58:21.280 --> 58:23.280
And Winnicott talks about when things become precongous.

58:23.280 --> 58:28.960
And anyway, along the way there's a lot of stuff.

58:28.960 --> 58:34.400
Until finally she gets to her being very fond of parties and parties which have this kind

58:34.400 --> 58:36.800
of represent they snoopy parties and so forth.

58:36.800 --> 58:42.240
And then her brother she said was having a party where there was a fireman theme.

58:42.240 --> 58:53.160
So I picked up on that and I said I heard that there was a sad fire in the family and

58:53.160 --> 58:54.680
there was a sad fire in the family.

58:54.680 --> 59:02.520
Okay, she says, yes, I said that they died so she spontaneously now tells me without my

59:02.520 --> 59:04.760
asking her about it.

59:04.760 --> 59:09.200
You know the sister did get out so there's some repair in the fact that not everybody

59:09.200 --> 59:10.200
went.

59:10.200 --> 59:12.000
I look at my daddy's surgery book.

59:12.000 --> 59:16.600
Now where did that come from?

59:16.600 --> 59:21.680
So you pay attention to the associated path and so forth as to what's going on.

59:21.680 --> 59:28.440
Now she had made reference to her father being a surgeon and he put people to sleep with

59:28.440 --> 59:30.560
what she calls sleepy air.

59:30.560 --> 59:36.480
And by the way, she remembers she has a sleep disturbance.

59:36.480 --> 59:41.160
I looked at my daddy's surgery book and the pictures of them doing dog surgery.

59:41.160 --> 59:50.240
My mother and Amy, these are fictitious names, had their appendixes out.

59:50.240 --> 59:51.960
Where does this come from?

59:51.960 --> 59:55.920
You sit there amazed as to where, what's happening here?

59:55.920 --> 59:56.920
Okay.

59:56.920 --> 01:00:03.040
I said, your mother and Amy, she said, well they only had to take it out if it's infected

01:00:03.040 --> 01:00:05.680
and you cut a hole in a blanket and then you're asleep.

01:00:05.680 --> 01:00:07.160
I saw my mother scar.

01:00:07.160 --> 01:00:10.760
I hear she's going on.

01:00:10.760 --> 01:00:13.440
I said, maybe you'd like to draw it.

01:00:13.440 --> 01:00:17.920
That's a picture.

01:00:17.920 --> 01:00:24.000
If she says to me, what if it comes out looking like a child?

01:00:24.000 --> 01:00:27.520
I'll leave it up to you as we go along to make the inferences.

01:00:27.520 --> 01:00:28.520
Okay.

